edu.nd.darts.cimon
Class CimonListAdapter

java.lang.Object
  android.widget.BaseExpandableListAdapter
      edu.nd.darts.cimon.CimonListAdapter
All Implemented Interfaces:
ExpandableListAdapter, HeterogeneousExpandableList
public class CimonListAdapter
extends BaseExpandableListAdapter

Adapter for listview in tabs of administration app. This adapter is used for the System, Sensor and User activity tabs of the administration app. It is an adapter for an expandable list view, where metrics are consolidated to metric groups, and the groups can be expanded to reveal the individual metrics.

This list view displays status of all actively monitored metrics, and provides ability for user to enable monitors directly in administration app.

Author:
darts
See Also:
NDroidAdmin, CimonListView

Constructor Detail

CimonListAdapter

public CimonListAdapter(Context context,
                        AdminObserver adminObserver)
Adapter for listview in tabs of administration app. This adapter is used for the System, Sensor and User activity tabs of the administration app. It is an adapter for an expandable list view, where metrics are consolidated to metric groups, and the groups can be expanded to reveal the individual metrics.

This list view displays status of all actively monitored metrics, and provides ability for user to enable monitors directly in administration app.

Parameters:
context - context for administration app
adminObserver - observer for this tab's category of metrics (system/sensor/user)

swapGroupCursor

public Cursor swapGroupCursor(Cursor cursor)
Swap in a new Cursor for the group data, returning the old Cursor. The returned old Cursor is not closed, this will be handled by the LoaderManager. If the new group cursor has different structure than previous cursor, existing children cursors will be released.

Parameters:
cursor - The new cursor to be used.
Returns:
Returns the previously set Cursor, or null if there was not one. If the given new Cursor is the same instance as the previously set Cursor, null is also returned.

swapChildrenCursor

public Cursor swapChildrenCursor(int groupId,
                                 Cursor childrenCursor)
Swap in new children Cursor for a particular group, returning the old Cursor. The returned old Cursor is not closed, this will be handled by the LoaderManager.

This is useful when asynchronously querying to prevent blocking the UI.

Parameters:
groupId - The group whose children are being set via this Cursor.
childrenCursor - The Cursor that contains the children of the group.
Returns:
Returns the previously set Cursor, or null if there was not one. If the given new Cursor is the same instance as the previously set Cursor, null is also returned.

updateGroup

public void updateGroup(int groupId)
Updates the view for a particular metric group. Updates are performed on individual groups, as new data is available, to avoid frequent refreshing of the entire list view, since this can be an expensive operation.

Parameters:
groupId - ID of the group with updated data

releaseCursorHelpers

private void releaseCursorHelpers()
Release all cached children cursors. This should only be necessary when the structure of the group cursor has changed, or if the listview is being released.
